Kubernetes Deployment Instructions

Build and Tag Docker Images:

file.sh
docker build -t product-service:1.0 ./product
docker build -t order-service:1.0 ./order
docker build -t user-service:1.0 ./user
docker build -t frontend-service:1.0 ./frontend




Push Docker Images to a Registry (e.g., Docker Hub):

file.sh
docker tag product-service:1.0 <your-dockerhub-username>/product-service:1.0
docker tag order-service:1.0 <your-dockerhub-username>/order-service:1.0
docker tag user-service:1.0 <your-dockerhub-username>/user-service:1.0
docker tag frontend-service:1.0 <your-dockerhub-username>/frontend-service:1.0

docker push <your-dockerhub-username>/product-service:1.0
docker push <your-dockerhub-username>/order-service:1.0
docker push <your-dockerhub-username>/user-service:1.0
docker push <your-dockerhub-username>/frontend-service:1.0





Deploy to Kubernetes:

file.sh
kubectl apply -f k8s/product-deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/order-deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/user-deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/frontend-deployment.yaml